## Commit message format

- commit message lines shouldn't be longer than 100 characters

```
<type>(<scope>) <subject>
<BLANK LINE>
<body>
<BLANK LINE>
```

## Subject Line

- contains succinct description of the change

### Type

- feature  (adding a feature)
- refactor (refactoring code)
- fix      (fixing a bug)
- test     (adding or changing tests)
- chore    (general maintaining tasks)
- style    (changing code style)

### Scope

- specifies the place or domain of the commit change

### Subject

- imperative, present tense
- uncapitalized first letter
- no dot at the end

## Body

- includes motivation for the change
- contrasts with previous behavior
